body:
I'm not sure if it would be cleaner to pull the locking into `ManagementListener.handleEvent` (making all of these called methods protected). Then, before the switch statement you could simply do:
```java
if (event == CACHE_CREATE || event == CACHE_REMOVE) {
  lock.writeLock.lock();
} else {
  lock.readlock.lock();
}
```
That way it's obvious at a glance what event requires which type of lock.
